,"post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-wisdom-al-hikmah","tag-brotherhood-al-ikhwah","tag-community-jamaah","tag-gentleness-al-rifq","tag-guarding-the-tongue","tag-manners-adab","tag-prophetic-virtues-manaqib-nabawi","tag-reputation-al-ird","tag-speech-al-qawl"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-v9","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":38549,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/12\/25\/tahajjud-awf\/","url_meta":{"origin":1931,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Tahajjud: Awf witnesses the Prophet\u2019s night prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 25, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Awf ibn Malik reported: I stood with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, to pray at night. The Prophet began to recite Surat al-Baqarah and he would not pass by a verse of mercy but that he would ask for it, nor did he pass by\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":29330,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/13\/sahabah-said-when-praised\/","url_meta":{"origin":1931,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Humility: What the companions said when praised","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Adi ibn Artah reported: When a man among the companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, was praised for his righteousness, he would say, \u201cO Allah, do not blame me for what they say and forgive me for what they do not know!\u201d Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36721,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/07\/27\/allah-guide-yahud\/","url_meta":{"origin":1931,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Sneezing: Response to a non-Muslim who sneezes","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Musa reported: The Jews used to sneeze in front of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, hoping that he would say, \u201cMay Allah have mercy on you.\u201d The Prophet would say, \u201cMay Allah guide you and amend your affairs.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2739 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":480,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/01\/31\/how-prophet-criticized-people\/","url_meta":{"origin":1931,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Manners: How the Prophet criticized people","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 31, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would not insult others, he would not use profanity, and he would not curse others. If he wanted to criticize one of us, he would say, \"What is the matter with him? His forehead be dusted!\" Source: \u1e62a\u1e25\u012b\u1e25\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14606,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/06\/06\/tawhid-then-muhammad-wills\/","url_meta":{"origin":1931,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Tawhid: What Allah wills, then what Muhammad wills","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Tufayl reported: A man among the idolaters said to a man among the Muslims, \"How excellent it would be of your people if you said: What Allah wills and Muhammad wills.\" The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, heard him and he said, \u201cDo not say: What Allah wills\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28821,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/08\/allah-no-need-punish-yourself\/","url_meta":{"origin":1931,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Vows: Allah does not need you to punish yourself","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, saw an old man walking with the support of his two sons. The Prophet said, \u201cWhat is the matter with this man?\u201d They said, \u201cHe has vowed to walk to the Ka\u2019bah.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cAllah does not need this\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1931","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],